  "prompt": "What online stores accept food stamps for delivery in FL?",
  "response": "As of the most recent information in October 2023, several online retailers accept food stamps (SNAP/EBT) for delivery in Florida. Here are some key options:\n\n1. **Amazon**: You can use your SNAP/EBT card to purchase eligible groceries on Amazon. Delivery options vary depending on your location.\n\n2. **Walmart**: Walmart accepts SNAP/EBT for online grocery orders. You can use their pickup and delivery services.\n\n3. **Instacart**: Instacart allows you to use SNAP/EBT for grocery delivery from participating retailers such as:\n   - Aldi\n   - Publix\n   - Price Chopper\n   - Food Lion\n   - And other local grocery stores depending on your area.\n\n4. **FreshDirect**: FreshDirect accepts SNAP/EBT for grocery delivery in some areas. Check availability in your area.\n\n5. **BJ's Wholesale Club**: BJ's accepts EBT for online grocery purchases, and delivery options vary by location.\n\nFor all the above services, it is best to check their websites for the latest updates and availability in your specific area. Always ensure that you are purchasing eligible items as not all grocery products can be bought using SNAP/EBT benefits. Delivery charges, fees, and non-eligible items must typically be paid with another form of payment.",
